                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14991261" author="yuhaoyan" created="Thu, 5 Nov 2015 07:20:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking into it. Should be a bug. Breeze may remove the extra end in colPtr after addition. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14992978" author="yuhaoyan" created="Fri, 6 Nov 2015 02:51:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems breeze will add extra 0 to value in CSCMatrix when adding two sparseMatrix and break the rule &quot;colPtr.last is always equal to rowIndices.length&quot;. Invoking compact should resolve the issue. I will run a few tests and send a fix if confirmed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14993440" author="apachespark" created="Fri, 6 Nov 2015 09:50:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;hhbyyh&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/9520&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/9520&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15103576" author="yuhaoyan" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2016 04:38:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A fix has been merged into Breeze. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/scalanlp/breeze/commit/d255b66d7e7720f8447a49c78e762d21b18835c3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/scalanlp/breeze/commit/d255b66d7e7720f8447a49c78e762d21b18835c3&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15205242" author="josephkb" created="Mon, 21 Mar 2016 21:59:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good to hear!  I am wondering though if it was a mistake to close your original PR (since the Breeze fix won&apos;t be put into Spark that quickly).  What do you think about re-opening your PR to get the bug fix into 2.0 and a few backports?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15205734" author="yuhaoyan" created="Tue, 22 Mar 2016 03:52:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure we can do it. About the fix, I assume we should copy first and invoke compact, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
